# Sudoers File

Used to grant access privileges

    Controls which users or groups can execute commands with elevated rights.
    Prevents the disclosure of the root password while allowing the execution of specific tasks.

Specific Permissions

    Allows the administrator to specify which commands a user can execute.

Security

    Reduces the risk of accidental or malicious system-wide modifications by limiting access to root.

To open the sudoers file: sudo visudo
